        <h2>Competition in Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu</h2>
        <p>
            BJJ competitions have become a global phenomenon. Major events like the IBJJF World Championships and ADCC test practitioners' skills in both gi and no-gi formats. Competitors must balance technique, stamina, and strategy to succeed, making these tournaments a true test of one's BJJ skills.
        </p>
        <p>
            Learn more about BJJ competitions:
            <a href="https://www.ibjjf.com/" target="_blank" style="color: white;">IBJJF</a>
        </p>
    </RadzenCard>
    <RadzenCard Style="background-color: var(--rz-success-darker); padding: 20px; color: white; grid-column: span 6;">
        <h2>The Mental Game of BJJ</h2>
        <p>
            BJJ is often referred to as a "human chess game" because of the mental strategies involved. Practitioners must anticipate their opponent's movements, stay calm under pressure, and adjust their approach constantly. The mental toughness gained through BJJ often carries over into other areas of life.
        </p>
        <p>
            Learn more about the mental aspect of BJJ:
            <a href="https://www.bjjee.com/" target="_blank" style="color: white;">BJJ Eastern Europe</a>
        </p>
    </RadzenCard>
    <RadzenCard Style="background-color: var(--rz-warning-darker); padding: 20px; color: white; grid-column: span 6;">
        <h2>BJJ in Mixed Martial Arts (MMA)</h2>
        <p>
            BJJ has long been a key component of MMA. Early pioneers like Royce Gracie showed the power of BJJ in real fights by using submissions to neutralize larger, stronger opponents. Today, every serious MMA fighter must have a solid understanding of Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu to compete at the highest levels.
        </p>
        <p>
            Learn more about BJJ in MMA:
            <a href="https://www.ufc.com/" target="_blank" style="color: white;">UFC</a>
        </p>
    </RadzenCard>
    <RadzenCard Style="background-color: var(--rz-secondary-darker); padding: 20px; color: white; grid-column: span 4;">
        <h2>Escapes and Sweeps</h2>
        <p>
            Escaping from bad positions and sweeping your opponent to gain the upper hand are essential skills in BJJ. Learning how to break free from submissions and reverse positions allows practitioners to remain calm under pressure and turn the tide in a match.
        </p>
        <p>
            Learn more about escapes and sweeps:
            <a href="https://www.bjjfanatics.com/" target="_blank" style="color: white;">BJJ Fanatics</a>
        </p>
